HEADWORD: Pharmacology
<hw>Phar`ma*col"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fa`rmakon</grk> drug + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pharmacologie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The science dealing
with knowledge of the preparation, use, and effects of drugs or
medicines; the art of preparing medicines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A treatise on the art of preparing
medicines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharmacomathy</ent>⟦br⟧
